3.) Run the App

Register Page:
/Identity/Account/Register

Login Page:
/Identity/Account/Login


4.) Add Login/Register Buttons
Open: Views/Shared/_Layout.cshtml

Add this in navbar:

<div class="d-flex">
    <a class="btn btn-outline-dark me-2" asp-area="Identity"
       asp-page="/Account/Login">
       Login
    </a>

    <a class="btn btn-dark" asp-area="Identity"
       asp-page="/Account/Register">
       Register
    </a>
</div>


5.) Show User Name After Login

Replace buttons with:

@if (User.Identity.IsAuthenticated)
{
    <span class="me-3">
        Hello @User.Identity.Name
    </span>

    <form method="post"
          asp-area="Identity"
          asp-page="/Account/Logout">

        <button class="btn btn-danger">
            Logout
        </button>
    </form>
}
else
{
    <a class="btn btn-outline-dark me-2"
       asp-area="Identity"
       asp-page="/Account/Login">
       Login
    </a>

    <a class="btn btn-dark"
       asp-area="Identity"
       asp-page="/Account/Register">
       Register
    </a>
}



